.SH NAME
SDL_WaitSemaphoreTimeout \- Wait until a semaphore has a positive value and then decrements it\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_mutex\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "bool SDL_WaitSemaphoreTimeout(SDL_Semaphore *sem, Sint32 timeoutMS);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
This function suspends the calling thread until either the semaphore
pointed to by
.BR sem
has a positive value or the specified time has elapsed\[char46]
If the call is successful it will atomically decrement the semaphore value\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I sem
the semaphore to wait on\[char46]
.TP
.I timeoutMS
the length of the timeout, in milliseconds, or -1 to wait indefinitely\[char46]
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns true if the wait succeeds or false if the wait times out\[char46]

